article.headline: Evansville 51, Ball St. 50
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Redshirt freshman Pieter van Tongeren's layup with 10 seconds left capped an Evansville comeback and lifted the Aces past Ball State 51-50 Saturday. Ball State (0-4) rallied from a 27-21 halftime deficit to go up by nine point, 47-38, on a Rashaun McLemore jumper with 4:55 left. von Tongeren responded with a dunk, Shy Ely hit a pair of jumpers, Jason Holsinger added a 3-pointer and Nate Garner a layup as the Aces (1-3) reeled off 11 straight points. Peyton Stovall hit a 3-pointer to put Ball State ahead 50-49 with 34 seconds left before von Tongeren hit the game-winner. Stovall led all scorers with 22 points, including 4-of-6 on 3-pointers. Malik Perry added 10 points for the Cardinals. Darin Granger came off the bench to lead Evansville with 16 points as Evansville's bench outscored Ball State's 24-10. Garner, also playing off the bench, finished with four points and a team-high 10 rebounds. von Tongeren finished with nine points and nine rebounds.
